selrach.bnetbuilder.model.variable
Class Factor

java.lang.Object
  selrach.bnetbuilder.model.variable.Factor

public class Factor
extends java.lang.Object

Factor object, its used when we are dealing with only transient variables. This represents an intermediate distribution that is a result of different inference algorithms. This is particularly targeted toward transient objects in the system.

Author:
Charles Robertson

complement

public Factor complement(Factor marginal,
                         java.util.Collection<TransientVariable> set)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
Calculates the complement of this factor given the marginal of this factor. We pass in the marginal simply because whenever we use this function, the marginal has already been calculated. This can be computed directly with just the set of variables
